name: fire-behavior-ignition-probability
notes: An ignition probability layer (fire density) was derived using an interpolation process (ArcInfo; pointinterp) of the fire start data. 2-km cells were used for the interpolation process because fire locations were commonly only reported to the nearest Public Land Survey Section (PLSS), approximately 1 square mile. Interpolation resulted in 2-km cells being attributed with the count of ignitions. Ignition probability was derived by classifying the density data into 5 classes (low to high) using the "natural break" algorithm included in ArcMap. The values represent relative values that have been standardized between 0.0 and 1.0
